history.description:
SMWLWX

The National Weather Service in Sterling Virginia has issued a

* Special Marine Warning for...
Chesapeake Bay from North Beach to Drum Point MD...
Chesapeake Bay from Pooles Island to Sandy Point MD...
Chesapeake Bay from Sandy Point to North Beach MD...
Chesapeake Bay north of Pooles Island MD...
Chester River to Queenstown MD...
Choptank River to Cambridge MD and the Little Choptank River...
Eastern Bay...
Patapsco River including Baltimore Harbor...

* Until midnight EDT.

* At 1022 PM EDT, strong thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 15 nm west of Middle River to 6 nm northeast of
Popes Creek, moving northeast at 35 knots.

HAZARD...Wind gusts 34 knots or greater.

SOURCE...Airport. A 34 knot gust was reported at Reagan National.

IMPACT...Boaters in small craft could be thrown overboard by
suddenly higher winds and waves capsizing their vessel.

* Locations impacted include...
Choptank River, Kent Narrows Bridge, North Point State Park,
Magothy River, Rock Hall, Chester River, Eastern Bay, Dobbins
Island, Blackwalnut Point, Pooles Island, Gunpowder River, Sandy
Point State Park, Northeast River, Bloody Point Light, Poplar
Island, Parsons Island, Fort Smallwood State Park, Pinehurst,
Turkey Point, and Knapps Narrows Bridge.

history.description:
SMWLWX

The National Weather Service in Sterling Virginia has issued a

* Special Marine Warning for...
Tidal Potomac from Cobb Island MD to Smith Point VA...

* Until midnight EDT.

* At 1025 PM EDT, strong thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near U.S. 301 Nice Memorial Bridge to 9 nm southwest
of Westmoreland State Park, moving east at 25 knots.

HAZARD...Wind gusts 34 knots or greater.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Boaters in small craft could be thrown overboard by
suddenly higher winds and waves capsizing their vessel.

* Locations impacted include...
Yeocomico River, Breton Bay, Saint Clements Bay, Piney Point, Mouth
Of The Potomac River, Point Lookout, Tall Timbers, Cobb Island,
Coltons Point, Nomini Bay, Coles Point, Saint George Island,
Wicomico River, and White Point Beach.

history.description:
SMWAKQ

The National Weather Service in Wakefield has issued a

* Special Marine Warning for...
James River from James River Bridge to Hampton Roads
Bridge-Tunnel...
James River from Jamestown to the James River Bridge...
Rappahannock River from Urbanna to Windmill Point...
York River...

* Until 1230 AM EDT.

* At 1029 PM EDT, gusty showers were located along a line extending
from 27 nm west of Urbanna Inlet to 25 nm west of Cobham Bay to 37
nm west of Burwell Bay, moving east at 35 knots.

HAZARD...Wind gusts to 40 knots.

SOURCE...Radar.

IMPACT...Small craft could be damaged in briefly higher winds and
suddenly higher waves.

* Showers will be near...
Urbanna Inlet and Cobham Bay around 1110 PM EDT.
Irvington around 1115 PM EDT.
Burwell Bay and White Stone Bridge around 1120 PM EDT.
Coleman Bridge around 1125 PM EDT.
James River Bridge around 1140 PM EDT.
Dominion Pier around 1145 PM EDT.
Monitor Merrimack Bridge Tunnel, Hampton Flats, and Hampton River
Inlet around 1150 PM EDT.
Sewells Point around 1155 PM EDT.

history.description:
At 1030 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from near Jordans Point to near Stony Creek to near
Littleton. Movement was east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small trees and blow around
unsecured objects. Wind impacting handling of high profile
vehicles.

Gusty showers will be near...
Emporia, Disputanta, Sussex, Jarratt, Stony Creek, Barley,
Garysville, and Radium around 1035 PM EDT.
Gaston, Green Plain, and Burrowsville around 1040 PM EDT.
Roanoke Rapids, Waverly, Claremont, Dahlia, Homeville, and Cabin
Point around 1045 PM EDT.
Claresville and Rustic around 1050 PM EDT.
Garysburg around 1055 PM EDT.
Wakefield, Seaboard, and Dendron around 1100 PM EDT.
Williamsburg, Surry, and Elberon around 1105 PM EDT.
College Of William And Mary, Ivor, Jamestown, Scotland, and Kings
Point around 1110 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Vicksville, Pons,
Grizzard, Gum Forks, Camp Peary, Henrico, Lumberton, Hilda, Dory, and
Poolesville.
